#Financial Modelling - Eicher Motots LTD 

## Project Scope

The analysis was conducted across five key dimensions:

Growth Analysis: Sales, EBITDA, EBIT, Net Profit, and Dividend Growth

Profitability Margins: Gross, EBITDA, EBIT, EBT, and Net Profit Margins

Cost & Operating Efficiency: Expense ratios and Operating Income trends

Return & Shareholder Metrics: ROCE, ROE, Retained Earnings, Sustainable Growth Rate, and Interest Coverage

Liquidity & Turnover Ratios: Debtor, Creditor, Inventory, Fixed Capital, and Overall Capital Turnover

## Key Insights
The company experienced a temporary slowdown in FY2021, followed by strong recovery from FY2022 onward.
Profitability margins improved structurally post recovery, reflecting better cost control and operational strength.
Return ratios (ROCE and ROE) rebounded significantly, indicating improved capital efficiency.
Interest coverage remained strong, highlighting low financial risk.
Asset utilization and working capital management showed steady improvement over the period.
Learning Outcomes
Interpreting financial ratios in a strategic business context
Connecting growth, profitability, and efficiency metrics
Identifying the financial impact of external disruptions
Performing trend analysis using statistical measures
Converting financial data into actionable business insights
This project demonstrates analytical capability in financial statement analysis and performance evaluation using structured ratio interpretation.
